---
/**
 * StackFutureProof — Section 7: Future-Proof Guarantees
 *
 * Standards timeline showing Web Components, Shadow DOM, CEM, DTCG, ES Modules,
 * plus a framework churn comparison sidebar.
 */
---

<style is:inline>
  /* ============================================
     SECTION 7: FUTURE-PROOF GUARANTEES
     ============================================ */
  .ts-future-section {
    background: var(--surface-0);
  }

  .ts-timeline {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-12);
  }

  .ts-timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 18px;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--wc-cyan), var(--wc-accent), var(--wc-green));
  }

  .ts-timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .ts-timeline-item:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .ts-timeline-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(-1 * var(--space-12) + 10px);
    top: 4px;
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 3px solid;
    background: var(--surface-0);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .ts-timeline-dot.ts-dot-cyan { border-color: var(--wc-cyan); box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.4); }
  .ts-timeline-dot.ts-dot-accent { border-color: var(--wc-accent); box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4); }
  .ts-timeline-dot.ts-dot-green { border-color: var(--wc-green); box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4); }
  .ts-timeline-dot.ts-dot-amber { border-color: var(--wc-amber); box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.4); }
  .ts-timeline-dot.ts-dot-electric { border-color: var(--wc-electric); box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4); }

  .ts-timeline-title {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .ts-timeline-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .ts-timeline-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .ts-tag-standard {
    background: rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.12);
    color: var(--wc-cyan);
  }

  .ts-tag-native {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.12);
    color: var(--wc-green);
  }

  .ts-tag-open {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.12);
    color: var(--wc-accent);
  }

  /* Framework churn contrast */
  .ts-churn-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-12) auto 0;
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--surface-3);
  }

  .ts-churn-title {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ts-churn-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .ts-churn-item {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ts-churn-item-label {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .ts-churn-item-versions {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .ts-churn-vs {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.15);
  }

  .ts-churn-vs-text {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--wc-cyan);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ts-timeline {
      padding-left: var(--space-10);
    }

    .ts-timeline::before {
      left: 14px;
    }

    .ts-timeline-dot {
      left: calc(-1 * var(--space-10) + 6px);
      width: 16px;
      height: 16px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .ts-churn-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

<section class="ts-section ts-future-section" aria-label="Future-proof guarantees">
  <div class="ts-section-inner">
    <div class="ts-section-header scroll-reveal">
      <span class="ts-section-label">Longevity</span>
      <h2 class="ts-section-title">This Stack Will Still Work in 2030</h2>
      <p class="ts-section-description">
        Every core technology is backed by a W3C standard, browser-native API,
        or open specification. No single vendor controls the stack.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ts-timeline scroll-reveal">
      <div class="ts-timeline-item">
        <div class="ts-timeline-dot ts-dot-cyan" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="ts-timeline-tag ts-tag-standard">W3C Standard</span>
        <h3 class="ts-timeline-title">Web Components (Custom Elements v1)</h3>
        <p class="ts-timeline-desc">
          A W3C standard since 2018, natively supported in all modern browsers.
          No polyfills needed for Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+.
          The browser IS the runtime -- no framework needed to render.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ts-timeline-item">
        <div class="ts-timeline-dot ts-dot-green" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="ts-timeline-tag ts-tag-native">Browser Native</span>
        <h3 class="ts-timeline-title">Shadow DOM + CSS Custom Properties</h3>
        <p class="ts-timeline-desc">
          Shadow DOM provides true encapsulation. CSS custom properties pierce
          through Shadow DOM, providing the only viable theming mechanism.
          Both are browser-native APIs that require zero library support.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ts-timeline-item">
        <div class="ts-timeline-dot ts-dot-accent" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="ts-timeline-tag ts-tag-open">Open Specification</span>
        <h3 class="ts-timeline-title">Custom Elements Manifest (CEM)</h3>
        <p class="ts-timeline-desc">
          An open community specification for documenting Web Component APIs.
          Machine-readable JSON that feeds Storybook, IDEs, and documentation systems.
          Not controlled by any single vendor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ts-timeline-item">
        <div class="ts-timeline-dot ts-dot-amber" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="ts-timeline-tag ts-tag-standard">W3C Standard</span>
        <h3 class="ts-timeline-title">W3C DTCG Design Tokens (2025.10)</h3>
        <p class="ts-timeline-desc">
          The W3C Design Tokens Community Group specification reached its first
          stable version in October 2025. Token files written today are forward-compatible
          with every tool that adopts the standard.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ts-timeline-item">
        <div class="ts-timeline-dot ts-dot-electric" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <span class="ts-timeline-tag ts-tag-native">Browser Native</span>
        <h3 class="ts-timeline-title">ES Modules</h3>
        <p class="ts-timeline-desc">
          Standard ES2021 modules shipped directly to the browser. No CommonJS, no UMD.
          Modern Drupal (10.3+) and all evergreen browsers support ES modules natively.
          The distribution format will never need a major migration.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Framework churn contrast -->
    <div class="ts-churn-container scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-2">
      <h3 class="ts-churn-title">
        Meanwhile, in Framework Land...
      </h3>
      <div class="ts-churn-grid">
        <div class="ts-churn-item">
          <div class="ts-churn-item-label">React</div>
          <div class="ts-churn-item-versions">16 &rarr; 17 &rarr; 18 &rarr; 19</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ts-churn-item">
          <div class="ts-churn-item-label">Angular</div>
          <div class="ts-churn-item-versions">12 &rarr; 13 &rarr; ... &rarr; 19</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ts-churn-item">
          <div class="ts-churn-item-label">Vue</div>
          <div class="ts-churn-item-versions">2 &rarr; 3 (breaking)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ts-churn-vs">
        <div class="ts-churn-vs-text">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          WC-2026: Web Components v1 -- unchanged since 2018, supported forever
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
